name: Hamilton County Health Department - Tennessee
tweet: You do not need to be a resident of these communities to be eligible. Please see the attached flyer for more details. For questions, call our hotline at 423-209-8383 or visit our online vaccine calendar at  https://t.co/Ms3B7CFIqq.

name: Hamilton County Health Department - Tennessee
tweet: The Health Department will be at East Lake Courts on December 1 giving free flu shots to those ages 18 and up. We will also be at College Hill Courts for a pediatric COVID-19 vaccine event on December 2 and return on December 8 for adult flu shots.  https://t.co/yeopSm4bQL

name: Hamilton County Health Department - Tennessee
tweet: Starting November 30th, Moderna booster shots will be offered at Tennessee Riverpark in addition to Pfizer primary and booster shots.  Please call our hotline at 423-209-8383 or visit our online calendar at  https://t.co/Ms3B7CFIqq if you have any questions.  https://t.co/TRrnKuRlEp

name: Hamilton County Health Department - Tennessee
tweet: To make an appointment, please visit  https://t.co/n7mCLytTVz or call 423-463-0051. This event is open to all children ages 5-11 and your child does not have to be a student of Hamilton County School system to be eligible

name: Hamilton County Health Department - Tennessee
tweet: Today, November 23rd, the Hamilton County Health Department will be partnering with Hamilton County Schools on another vaccination event for children ages 5-11. This event will be held at East Ridge Elementary, by appointment only, from 4:00 p.m. to 7:00 p.m.  https://t.co/XVbC2UnRc1

name: Hamilton County Health Department - Tennessee
tweet: As a special surprise, children were greeted and supported by Obi Wan, a therapy pet from Love on a Leash. Obi brought a positive experience and joy to our young visitors, parents and staff. For more information and to see other events, visit  https://t.co/Ms3B7CFIqq

name: Hamilton County Health Department - Tennessee
tweet: Thank you to our dedicated staff and volunteers for working this past Saturday, at our pediatric COVID-19 vaccine event! The event was a huge success and involved a lot of hard work from everyone involved.  https://t.co/entHCzflFk

name: Hamilton County Health Department - Tennessee
tweet: Beginning Monday, November 22nd, no appointments will be necessary for pediatric Pfizer vaccinations at the 921 E. 3rd St. Health Department location. Vaccination hours will remain Monday – Friday, 8:30 a.m. – 3:30 p.m.  https://t.co/TAqin1Y2sX

tweet: The Hamilton County Health Department and our COVID-19 vaccination sites will be closed next week Thursday, November 25th and Friday, November 26th for the Thanksgiving holiday. If you have questions, please call our hotline at 423-209-8383.  https://t.co/UCDZun6HzS

tweet: This event will be on November 20th at our East 3rd St Facility, from 9:00 a.m. to 2:00 p.m. For any questions and to make an appointment, please call our hotline at 423-209-8383 or visit our website at  https://t.co/Ms3B7Co71Q.
